Compounding of interest allows a principal amount to grow at a faster rate than simple interest, which is calculated as a percentage of only the principal amount.ÃÂ  source: Investopedia.

The effect of compounding depends on the frequency with which interest is compounded and the periodic interest rate which is applied.

Compound interest may be contrasted with simple interest, where interest is not added to the principal (there is no compounding).

